  "Aftersales Pairing : CID": {
   "width": 12060,
   "height": 10980,
   "color": "rgb(0,64,128)",
   "labels": [
    {
     "text": "Protected Pairing : Customer ID pairing in After Sales ",
     "color": "rgb(39,198,216)",
     "alignment": "2",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(64,0,64)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 120,
      "top": 0,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 11865
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "@Arial Unicode MS",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "Procedure",
     "color": "rgb(179,230,240)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 120,
      "top": 1920,
      "height": 5760,
      "width": 11880
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "@Arial Unicode MS",
      "size": 10.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "1) Approach the customer ID to the Kazashi ring and press the button \"CID Analyse\" to check its presence and status",
     "color": "rgb(179,230,240)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 120,
      "top": 2400,
      "height": 240,
      "width": 8760
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "@Arial Unicode MS",
      "size": 8.0,
      "bold": "0",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "2) Complete PARAMETER_CID_PAIRING (8 bytes, IDE1;IDE2) and press \"Request Server CID pairing\"",
     "color": "rgb(179,230,240)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 120,
      "top": 2760,
      "height": 600,
      "width": 8760
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "@Arial Unicode MS",
      "size": 8.0,
      "bold": "0",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "3) Select the \"Input Data Server\" (19 bytes) and copy it in the application \"Pairing using DDT2000\" ",
     "color": "rgb(179,230,240)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 120,
      "top": 3360,
      "height": 240,
      "width": 8760
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "@Arial Unicode MS",
      "size": 8.0,
      "bold": "0",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "5) Complete the \"Additional pairing data\" (optional) get the \"Server Answer\" from \"Pairing DDT2000\" and press \"Transmit Server Answer\" ",
     "color": "rgb(179,230,240)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 120,
      "top": 4080,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 11880
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "@Arial Unicode MS",
      "size": 8.0,
      "bold": "0",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "6) If the BCM is SA unlocked for CID pairing, approach a blank CID to the ring and press the button \"CID pairing\"  ",
     "color": "rgb(179,230,240)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 5880,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 10920
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "@Arial Unicode MS",
      "size": 8.0,
      "bold": "0",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "7) Repeat Step 6 for all CID to pair",
     "color": "rgb(179,230,240)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 7080,
      "height": 240,
      "width": 6840
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "@Arial Unicode MS",
      "size": 8.0,
      "bold": "0",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "CID / BCM information",
     "color": "rgb(240,236,179)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 6480,
      "top": 7800,
      "height": 3000,
      "width": 4770
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "MS Sans Serif",
      "size": 8.25,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
